## 2. Typography

Three font families are used, each with a specific role. Never substitute or mix these.

| Family | Variable | Role |
|---|---|---|
| Outfit | `--font-sans` | Default body, labels, buttons, nav, metadata |
| Fraunces | `--font-serif` | Display values: page titles, KPI numbers, metric values |
| JetBrains Mono | `--font-mono` | Codes, dates, small metadata, timeline labels |

### Type Scale

| Token | Size | Weight | Font | Usage |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Page title | 28px | 600 | serif | Screen/page heading (`letter-spacing: -0.3px`, `line-height: 1.2`) |
| Subtitle | 14px | 300 | sans | Page description under title |
| KPI value | 22px | 600 | serif | Hero metric numbers in KPI cards |
| Metric value | 18px | 600 | serif | Values inside detail cards (Financial, Time) |
| Card section title | 11px | 600 | sans | Card `<h3>` headers — ALL CAPS, `letter-spacing: 0.9px` |
| Client name | 14px | 600 | sans | Primary entity name in client card |
| Body / activity text | 13–14px | 400 | sans | Table rows, activity entries, general content |
| Button text | 13px | 500 | sans | All button labels |
| Labels / badge text | 11–12px | 500 | sans | Status badges, tags, KPI labels — often ALL CAPS |
| Metadata / dates | 11–12px | 400–500 | mono | Gantt dates, activity dates, days-elapsed |

