## 5. Color Semantics — Days Left

The "days left" indicator changes color based on urgency:

```js
function daysColor(daysLeft) {
  if (daysLeft > 14) return 'var(--c-green)';
  if (daysLeft >= 7) return 'var(--c-amber)';
  return 'var(--c-red)';
}
```

Icon circle background uses the same color at 18% opacity: `${daysColor(d)}18` (hex) or set alpha via `oklch(... / 18%)`.

---

## 6. Animation Principles

All animations use `cubic-bezier(.4, 0, .2, 1)` (standard ease-in-out).

| Element | Property | Duration | Delay |
|---|---|---|---|
| Page header | `opacity` + `translateY(10px)` | 400ms | 0ms |
| KPI row | `opacity` + `translateY(12px)` | 500ms | 100ms |
| Two-col grid | `opacity` + `translateY(14px)` | 500ms | 200ms |
| Bottom section | `opacity` + `translateY(14px)` | 500ms | 350ms |
| Activity rows | `opacity` + `translateX(-6px)` | 400ms | 350ms + `i × 70ms` |
| Circular progress | `stroke-dashoffset` | 1000ms | 120ms |
| Profit bar fill | `width` | 1200ms | mount |
| Gantt fill | `width` | 1000ms | mount |
| KPI hover overlay | `opacity` | 200ms | — |
| Button hover | `background`, `box-shadow` | 150ms | — |
| Tab hover | `color` | 150ms | — |

All enter animations are triggered by adding an `.in` class after a 50ms `setTimeout` on mount.

